President Trump congratulated General Charles Q. Brown Jr. on his confirmation as Chief of Staff of the Air Force during a ceremony in the Oval Office. Trump expressed his pride and honored Brown's achievements, noting that he was confirmed by a vote of 98 to nothing. Brown thanked the President and expressed his gratitude to his family for their support. Vice President Mike Pence administered the oath of office, and Secretary of Defense Mark Esper and outgoing Chief of Staff of the Air Force General David Goldfein also spoke at the ceremony. Trump praised the Air Force's capabilities and equipment, including the F-35s. The ceremony concluded with congratulations to General Brown and his family.